[EXTERNAL EMAIL]

Good morning everyone,
This is just a reminder that your slides are due today by 5pm! I look forwa=
rd to seeing you all on Wednesday.

Thanks,

Dr. Amy Hyman
DPEM Program Director & Associate Professor
Department of Health Sciences & Risk Management
________________________________
From: Amy Hyman
Sent: Monday, June 8, 2026 2:40 PM
To: jyevuy1@lsu.edu <jyevuy1@lsu.edu>; jjuli014@fiu.edu <jjuli014@fiu.edu>;=
 nasimyeganeh@ufl.edu <nasimyeganeh@ufl.edu>; u1533291@umail.utah.edu <u153=
3291@umail.utah.edu>; haifeng.wang@wsu.edu <haifeng.wang@wsu.edu>
Subject: NHC 2026 Researchers Meeting Session Coordination

Hello everyone,
I hope you all are doing well and are getting excited about next week=92s 2=
026 Natural Hazards Researchers Meeting. Here are some key details for our =
session.

Session Title: TRANSLATING COMPLEXITY: ASSESSMENT MODELS AND MARKETS IN A C=
HANGING CLIMATE
Date: Wednesday, June 17th
Time: 2:30-4:00pm MDT
Location: Fir

Presentation Slides

  *   Final slide files are due by EOD on Monday, June 15th.
     *
Upload your slides file into this Google folder<https://urldefense.com/v3/_=
_https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1L7zcOzoEa1F_ZcI0u5VWluuDXeMQvtxP__=
;!!PirnAJVEmx4jpg!_4wYLPJ6uVnOvllyyXXjQMXajRYeNMWfomjiw8nnEUIJFH0_yuWbRA-W8=
oR5a_h2i8JFDUWYAjPXhZUW$> <https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://drive.google=
.com/drive/folders/1L7zcOzoEa1F_ZcI0u5VWluuDXeMQvtxP__;!!PirnAJVEmx4jpg!_4w=
YLPJ6uVnOvllyyXXjQMXajRYeNMWfomjiw8nnEUIJFH0_yuWbRA-W8oR5a_h2i8JFDUWYAjPXhZ=
UW$> under the name of the session: =93TRANSLATING COMPLEXITY: ASSESSMENT M=
ODELS AND MARKETS IN A CHANGING CLIMATE"
     *
For consistency, please use the following file title format: "YOUR LAST NAM=
E-YOUR FIRST NAME"_"YOUR PRESENTATION TITLE"
     *
This is rare, but depending on the set-up there is a slight possibility tha=
t you may not be able to see your presenter notes from PPT when presenting.
     *
We recommend having them printed out or available on another device needed =
for reference.
  *
The Natural Hazards Center will ensure that live caption is turned on for a=
ll PowerPoint slides, to ensure audio accessibility.
  *
Your slides will be loaded and set-up on the computers in the session rooms=
 in advance; you will not need to present from your own laptop, but again, =
you might consider having access to it if you have notes in your slides.


Research Presentation Sessions

  *
Moderators, as well as presenters and panelists, should arrive in the room =
of your session at least 5 minutes before the session=92s start time.
  *
The flow for Research Presentations is as follows:
     *
Moderator will briefly introduce the session including its topic and format=
.
     *
Presenters will present their research for 10 minutes each in the order des=
ignated on the Researchers Meeting schedule. Please follow that order as so=
me people move session to session to see different presentations.  The agen=
da can be located here<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://hazards.colorado=
.edu/workshop/2026/researchers-meeting/translating-complexity-assessment-mo=
dels-and-markets-in-a-changing-climate__;!!JmPEgBY0HMszNaDT!viinU1YZtl8Dd1A=
1_cUZqq3oYz3XvId_iKW4h8bb5ulKssBSnElq_h4M67zvT_9b_NQFLFCZ_BGCm34HPULK$>.
     *
Questions will be held until after all presentations are complete.
     *
After the research presentations, as the moderator, I will turn to the audi=
ence for questions. In case the audience is initially quiet, I will have a =
question or two ready to go (but please privilege the audience questions, f=
irst, to ensure engagement).
     *
As I close the session, I will make sure to thank all the panelists, the st=
udent volunteer, and the audience members for their participation!

I look forward to seeing you all at the session. Please feel free to reach =
out if you have any questions.

Safe travels next week!
Amy


[signature_529919419]Dr. Amy Hyman
DPEM Program Director & Associate Professor
